00:11.261 --> 00:12.887
<i>ROCKO'S MODERN LIFE.</i>

00:18.768 --> 00:22.439
♪ ROCKO'S MODERN LIFE ♪

00:22.522 --> 00:24.441
<i>ROCKO'S MODERN LIFE.</i>

00:24.524 --> 00:27.193
(<i> whistling and buzzing</i> )

00:27.819 --> 00:28.862
(<i> splat!</i> )

00:29.362 --> 00:29.904
(<i> screaming</i> )

00:29.988 --> 00:33.700
♪ ROCKO'S MODERN LIFE. ♪

00:33.783 --> 00:35.827
<i>ROCKO'S MODERN LIFE.</i>

00:37.036 --> 00:42.125
[Captioning sponsored by THE
U.S. DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION]

00:42.208 --> 00:44.627
THAT WAS A HOOT!

00:57.515 --> 01:01.603
{\an5}Rocko (<i> reading</i> ):
"FROM THE MOMENT
HE FIRST LAID EYES ON AGNES

01:01.686 --> 01:03.980
"REALLY, REALLY BIG MAN
KNEW IT WAS LOVE AT FIRST SIGHT.

01:04.063 --> 01:06.816
"OH, AGNES,
TO PROVE MY LOVE FOR YOU

01:06.900 --> 01:08.860
"I WOULD SWIM
THE HIGHEST MOUNTAIN.

01:08.943 --> 01:10.570
"OR CLIMB THE DEEPEST SEA

01:10.653 --> 01:12.489
"I'D EVEN PUT ON
THIS CHICKEN SUIT

01:12.572 --> 01:13.531
"AND DANCE THE TANGO

01:13.615 --> 01:16.701
{\an1}IN A VAT OF EGG SALAD
TO SHOW MY LOVE FOR YOU"?

01:16.785 --> 01:19.162
YOU'VE GOT TO BE JOKING!

01:19.245 --> 01:20.455
THAT'S JUST STUPID.

01:20.538 --> 01:22.540
I'D NEVER DO ANYTHING CRAZY
TO IMPRESS A WOMAN.

01:22.624 --> 01:25.293
(<i> rings</i> )

01:37.055 --> 01:38.056
(<i> clears throat</i> )

01:38.139 --> 01:40.308
HI! I'D LIKE TO BUY
THIS WEEK'S ISSUE OF

01:40.391 --> 01:42.560
<i>ROLLER DERBY WOMEN</i>
<i>FROM PLANET 12</i>

01:42.644 --> 01:44.229
FEATURING TWINKIE,
THE WONDER WORM.

01:44.312 --> 01:45.188
{\an3}SURE.

01:45.271 --> 01:48.942
(<i> hemming and hawing</i> )

01:52.445 --> 01:54.364
HELLO?

01:54.447 --> 01:55.907
ARE YOU OKAY?

01:55.990 --> 01:58.701
(<i> stammering</i> )

01:58.785 --> 02:02.539
WELL... HERE'S MY MONEY.

02:02.622 --> 02:07.168
I'LL JUST, UH,
LEAVE IT ON THE COUNTER.

02:07.252 --> 02:08.752
WELL, THANKS.

02:08.836 --> 02:09.711
BYE, NOW.

02:09.795 --> 02:10.713
(<i> bell rings</i> )

02:10.797 --> 02:11.756
HI, SHEILA.

02:11.840 --> 02:12.173
HI, HEFF.

02:12.257 --> 02:12.549
BYE, SHEILA.

02:12.632 --> 02:14.092
{\an1}BYE, HEFF.

02:14.175 --> 02:14.884
BYE, BYE.

02:14.968 --> 02:17.053
BYE, BYE...
BYE, NOW.

02:17.137 --> 02:17.470
(<i> babbling</i> )

02:17.554 --> 02:19.389
{\an1}WHAT'S UP?

02:19.472 --> 02:22.058
BYE, BYE, BYE,
BYE, BYE.

02:22.141 --> 02:23.059
{\an1}ROCKO?

02:23.143 --> 02:24.143
HEY, ARE YOU

02:24.227 --> 02:25.395
{\an1}IN SOME KIND
OF TRANCE OR SOMETHING?

02:25.478 --> 02:27.397
{\an1}ROCKO?

02:27.480 --> 02:28.481
SNAP OUT OF IT!

02:28.565 --> 02:30.400
OH, NO!

02:30.483 --> 02:32.402
HE LOOKS LOVE-STRUCK!

02:32.485 --> 02:33.403
BYE, BYE, BYE.

02:33.486 --> 02:34.612
BYE, BYE, BYE...

02:34.696 --> 02:36.573
(<i> coughing, gagging</i> )

02:36.656 --> 02:38.449
{\an1}WOW, YOU WERE
REALLY OUT OF IT.

02:38.533 --> 02:40.201
HEFF, THAT DREAM ON WHEELS?

02:40.285 --> 02:41.202
YOU KNOW HER?

02:41.286 --> 02:42.287
WHO, SHEILA?

02:42.370 --> 02:43.746
SURE, I KNOW HER.

02:43.830 --> 02:46.416
SHE'S ONE OF THE REGULARS
DOWN AT THE ROLL-O-DOME.

02:46.499 --> 02:49.043
{\an1}I DIDN'T KNOW YOU
WERE INTO ROLLER SKATING.

02:50.044 --> 02:51.004
(<i> crashing</i> )

02:51.087 --> 02:52.255
OH, YEAH

02:52.338 --> 02:55.174
{\an1}I'M INTO A LOT OF STUFF
THAT YOU DON'T KNOW ABOUT.

02:55.258 --> 02:56.217
KILT TOSSING...

02:56.301 --> 02:57.176
RAT CURLING...

02:57.260 --> 02:58.928
SKUNK MINING...

02:59.012 --> 03:00.763
GEE, HOW INTERESTING, SAY...

03:00.847 --> 03:01.806
COULD YOU INTRODUCE ME
TO SHEILA?

03:01.890 --> 03:05.226
WELL, SURE, BUT...

03:05.310 --> 03:07.020
OH, I GET IT!

03:07.103 --> 03:08.438
ROCKO'S IN LOVE!

03:08.521 --> 03:09.689
I AM NOT!

03:09.772 --> 03:11.941
♪ ROCKO LOVES SHEILA ♪

03:12.025 --> 03:13.943
♪ ROCKO AND SHEILA ♪

03:14.027 --> 03:16.029
♪ SITTING IN A TREE... ♪

03:16.112 --> 03:17.030
{\an1}KISSING!

03:17.113 --> 03:17.989
HEFFER!

03:18.072 --> 03:20.617
OOPS. SORRY.

03:20.700 --> 03:21.868
IF YOU WANT TO MEET HER

03:21.951 --> 03:23.119
YOU SHOULD COME DOWN
TO THE RINK WITH ME.

03:23.202 --> 03:26.497
GEE, HEFF, I'VE NEVER
ROLLER SKATED BEFORE.

03:26.581 --> 03:27.790
I'D LOOK LIKE AN IDIOT.

03:27.874 --> 03:29.459
I CAN TEACH YOU.

03:29.542 --> 03:31.002
IT'D BE A HOOT!

03:32.211 --> 03:35.298
{\an1}Heffer:
YOU'LL HAVE A SWELL TIME.

03:35.381 --> 03:39.344
SKATING IS A LOT MORE HIP
THAN MOST PEOPLE REALIZE.

03:39.427 --> 03:40.720
HEY, KING.

03:40.803 --> 03:42.055
HI, WENDELL.
TWO, PLEASE.

03:42.138 --> 03:43.264
{\an1}"KING"?

03:43.348 --> 03:45.642
THAT'S WHAT
THEY CALL ME HERE.

03:45.725 --> 03:47.644
WELCOME TO MY DOMAIN.

03:47.727 --> 03:49.646
IT'S THE KING, WOW!

03:49.729 --> 03:51.189
OH, HE'S SO GRACEFUL!

03:51.272 --> 03:52.857
IT'S THE KING!
IT'S REALLY HIM.

03:52.941 --> 03:58.196
{\an1}GEE, MR. ROLLER SKATING KING,
MAY I HAVE YOUR ROYAL SIGNATURE?

03:58.279 --> 04:01.783
{\an1}WELL, THESE RENTAL SKATES
SEEM VERY NICE.

04:01.866 --> 04:03.952
I'M A WALLABY ON WHEELS.

04:04.035 --> 04:05.036
TERRIFIC!

04:07.872 --> 04:08.706
OOF!

04:08.790 --> 04:11.626
{\an1}THIS IS GOING TO BE HARDER
THAN I THOUGHT.

04:11.709 --> 04:14.587
YOU'LL DO BETTER
WHEN WE GET ON THE RINK.

04:17.757 --> 04:20.218
OKAY, ALL SKATE.

04:21.678 --> 04:23.388
{\an1}TRY NOT
TO FLAIL SO MUCH.

04:23.471 --> 04:25.139
NOW BACKWARDS.

04:25.682 --> 04:27.767
BE THE SKATES, ROCK.

04:27.850 --> 04:29.519
SKATE ON YOUR HANDS.

04:29.602 --> 04:31.688
{\an1}TRY TO GET ALL FIVE
OF YOUR STOMACHS

04:31.771 --> 04:32.939
{\an1}EVENLY DISTRIBUTED
OVER THE SKATES.

04:33.022 --> 04:35.274
SKATE ON YOUR NOSE.

04:35.358 --> 04:37.735
(<i> muffled</i> ):
PUT YOUR NOSTRILS INTO IT.

04:37.819 --> 04:40.196
SKATE ALL WILLY-NILLY
LIKE AN IDIOT.

04:40.279 --> 04:42.031
NOW YOU'RE GETTING IT!

04:45.076 --> 04:46.536
DON'T WORRY, ROCK.

04:46.619 --> 04:50.081
{\an1}YOU'RE DOING PRETTY GOOD
FOR A FIRST TIME.

04:50.164 --> 04:53.501
{\an1}I JUST WANT TO LOOK COOL
ON THESE BEFORE SHEILA SEES ME.

04:53.584 --> 04:55.253
HI, SHEILA.

04:56.379 --> 04:57.547
WHO'S YOUR FRIEND?

04:57.630 --> 04:57.922
THAT'S ROCKO.

04:58.006 --> 04:59.549
HI, ROCKO.

04:59.632 --> 05:00.550
NICE TO MEET YOU.

05:00.633 --> 05:03.261
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING DOWN THERE?

05:03.344 --> 05:04.512
OH. HEH, HEH.

05:04.595 --> 05:06.681
I WAS, UM, HEH-HEH,
EXERCISING.

05:06.764 --> 05:11.394
99, 100...

05:11.477 --> 05:12.854
ATTENTION, SKATERS.

05:12.937 --> 05:15.314
THIS NEXT SKATE
IS A SADIE HAWKINS

05:15.398 --> 05:17.150
SO IT'S LADIES' CHOICE.

05:17.233 --> 05:18.693
HEY, ROCKO, WOULD YOU
LIKE TO SKATE WITH ME?

05:18.776 --> 05:20.695
UH, ME?

05:20.778 --> 05:23.281
WELL, I, UH...

05:23.364 --> 05:23.740
HEH-HEH.

05:23.823 --> 05:26.367
HE'D LOVE TO!

05:26.451 --> 05:27.410
{\an1}WHA...?

05:27.493 --> 05:29.245
{\an1}BUT FIRST WE GOT TO GO
TO THE BATHROOM.

05:29.328 --> 05:31.164
{\an1}BUT I DON'T HAVE TO
GO TO THE...

05:31.247 --> 05:32.331
YES, YOU DO.

05:36.335 --> 05:38.921
{\an1}GEE, ROCKO,
YOU'RE A SMOOTH SKATER.

05:39.005 --> 05:40.590
THANKS.
YOU'RE GREAT, TOO.

05:40.673 --> 05:42.759
{\an1}IT'S LIKE YOUR SKATES
DON'T EVEN TOUCH THE GROUND.

05:42.842 --> 05:44.677
HEH-HEH. YEAH.

05:45.845 --> 05:46.846
Deejay:
Ladies and gentlemen

05:46.929 --> 05:51.309
please clear the floor
for our spotlight show.

05:53.394 --> 05:55.521
HERE, I'LL BE BACK IN A MINUTE.

05:55.605 --> 05:56.522
FOR YOUR VIEWING PLEASURE

05:56.606 --> 06:00.193
WE ARE PLEASED TO PRESENT
THE SKATE STYLINGS

06:00.276 --> 06:02.445
of the King!

06:02.528 --> 06:05.990
(<i> cheering, girls screaming</i> )

06:06.074 --> 06:10.036
(<i> "Blue Danube" waltz playing</i> )

06:10.119 --> 06:11.287
THAT'S HIM, IT'S HIM.

06:11.370 --> 06:13.956
{\an1}OH, SEE HOW GRACEFUL
HE IS ON THOSE WHEELS!

06:14.040 --> 06:17.126
(<i> cheering continues</i> )

06:17.210 --> 06:23.299
(<i> "Blue Danube" continues</i> )

06:23.382 --> 06:25.802
HE'S TERRIFIC!

06:25.885 --> 06:30.681
{\an1}(<i> "Blue Danube" ends,</i>
<i>crowd cheers</i> )

06:30.765 --> 06:34.310
(<i> disco music begins</i> )

06:42.735 --> 06:45.571
(<i> crowd cheering</i> )

06:49.283 --> 06:53.579
(<i> hard-driving rock tune</i> )

06:53.663 --> 06:56.874
(<i> rock music continues</i> )

07:07.218 --> 07:08.970
WOW! LOOK AT HIM GO!

07:09.053 --> 07:11.180
ISN'T THAT IMPRESSIVE?

07:11.264 --> 07:16.686
{\an1}WELL, IT'S NOT THAT IMPRESSIVE,
I MEAN... I COULD DO THAT.

07:16.769 --> 07:19.438
YEAH! I COULD
EVEN DO BETTER.

07:24.944 --> 07:26.362
EXCUSE ME, SIR.

07:26.445 --> 07:28.698
WHAT'S THE MOST IMPRESSIVE
SKATING TRICK YOU'VE GOT?

07:28.781 --> 07:30.575
THAT'D BE
THE OBSTACLE COURSE.

07:30.658 --> 07:32.118
WELL, I'D LIKE TO TRY IT!

07:32.201 --> 07:33.244
OKAY.

07:35.204 --> 07:35.997
(<i> whirring, humming</i> )

07:36.080 --> 07:39.333
(<i> clanking</i> )

07:48.426 --> 07:51.929
WOW, THAT LOOKS WAY
TOO DANGEROUS.

07:52.013 --> 07:52.930
BUT I CAN'T BACK OUT NOW.

07:53.014 --> 07:55.892
WHAT WOULD SHEILA THINK?

07:55.975 --> 07:57.393
OH, WHAT SHOULD I DO?

07:57.476 --> 08:00.521
Announcer:
It's the heart against the brain

08:00.605 --> 08:01.981
ladies and gentlemen!

08:02.064 --> 08:05.902
In the red corner, representing
emotions and infatuation

08:05.985 --> 08:07.904
Rocko's heart!

08:07.987 --> 08:09.655
In the gray corner

08:09.739 --> 08:13.409
{\an1}fighting for logic
and self-preservation

08:13.492 --> 08:14.744
Rocko's brain!

08:14.827 --> 08:16.078
(<i> bell rings</i> )

08:16.162 --> 08:18.289
And there's the bell!

08:18.372 --> 08:21.209
{\an1}It's a knockout,
ladies and gentlemen!

08:21.292 --> 08:23.711
Emotions win
over self-preservation.

08:27.882 --> 08:28.341
(<i> screeches to halt</i> )

08:28.424 --> 08:30.009
NICE ROUTINE, HEFF.

08:30.092 --> 08:31.594
THANKS. WHERE'S ROCKO?

08:31.677 --> 08:33.261
{\an1}HE'S GOING TO DO
THE OBSTACLE COURSE.

08:33.346 --> 08:34.388
WHAT?!

08:37.850 --> 08:41.437
MAYBE I COULD JUST GO
BACK DOWN THE LADDER.

08:41.520 --> 08:43.563
WAIT... WHY AM I MOVING?

09:21.727 --> 09:22.979
Heff:
WAY TO GO, ROCK!

09:25.189 --> 09:26.107
OH, NO!

09:26.190 --> 09:27.942
HE CAN'T STOP!

09:28.025 --> 09:32.280
AND IT'S DOWNHILL ALL THE WAY
TO THE O-TOWN BOTTOMLESS PIT!

09:32.363 --> 09:33.197
PROGRAMS!

09:33.281 --> 09:34.532
CAN'T TELL THE BOTTOMLESS PIT

09:34.615 --> 09:35.157
FROM A HOLE IN THE GROUND

09:35.241 --> 09:37.285
WITHOUT YOUR PROGRAM!

09:37.368 --> 09:39.287
I'VE GOT TO SAVE HIM.

09:49.630 --> 09:50.506
ROCKO?

09:50.589 --> 09:51.882
GIVE ME YOUR HAND.

09:51.966 --> 09:53.968
NOW, NOW, JUST LET ME
DO ALL THE WORK.

09:54.051 --> 09:55.845
HEFF! HURRY!

09:55.928 --> 09:58.347
THERE'S ROAD CONSTRUCTION AHEAD!

09:58.431 --> 10:00.182
NOT YET!

10:00.266 --> 10:01.517
{\an1}HEFF!

10:03.227 --> 10:05.771
WOW! THAT WAS CLOSE.

10:10.359 --> 10:12.445
OH, NO!
HEFF'S OUT OF CONTROL!

10:12.528 --> 10:14.071
I'VE GOT TO STOP HIM!

10:16.073 --> 10:19.035
{\an1}EXCUSE ME,
COULD I BORROW YOUR JACKHAMMER?

10:19.118 --> 10:20.536
SURE, LITTLE FELLA.

10:20.620 --> 10:22.455
DO YOU KNOW
HOW TO USE IT?

10:22.538 --> 10:24.665
DO <i> I</i> KNOW HOW TO USE IT?!

10:26.625 --> 10:28.627
WOW! HE'S GOOD.

10:30.254 --> 10:31.881
HEFF, WAKE UP!

10:36.302 --> 10:37.678
WELL, THAT'S NOT GOING TO WORK.

10:58.616 --> 11:01.285
WELL, THAT WAS CLOSE.

11:01.369 --> 11:04.288
ROCKO, THAT WAS WONDERFUL!

11:04.372 --> 11:06.082
YOU SAVED HEFF!

11:06.165 --> 11:09.085
{\an1}WELL, HEH,
HE SAVED ME FIRST.

11:09.168 --> 11:11.879
LOOK, SHEILA,
I HAVE A CONFESSION TO MAKE.

11:11.962 --> 11:13.756
I'M NOT REALLY A GOOD SKATER.

11:13.839 --> 11:16.634
THE TRUTH IS,
I JUST WANTED TO IMPRESS YOU.

11:16.717 --> 11:17.259
YOU'RE A NICE GUY, ROCKO.

11:17.343 --> 11:19.720
THAT'S WHAT IMPRESSES ME.

11:19.804 --> 11:21.180
I WILL SAY THIS, THOUGH.

11:21.263 --> 11:23.682
YOU SURE KNOW
HOW TO HANDLE A JACKHAMMER.

11:23.766 --> 11:26.018
THANKS. IT'S A HOBBY.

11:26.102 --> 11:28.187
ARE YOU INTERESTED
IN JACKHAMMERING?

11:28.270 --> 11:31.524
HEY!
I'M SITTING ON TOP OF THE WORLD!

11:31.607 --> 11:33.442
(<i> laughing</i> )

11:33.526 --> 11:34.610
TOP OF THE WORLD, MA!

11:34.693 --> 11:35.611
(<i> laughing</i> )

11:35.694 --> 11:37.113
(<i> cracking</i> )

11:37.196 --> 11:39.448
(<i> screaming</i> )

11:39.532 --> 11:41.617
(<i> Heff screaming</i> )

11:39.532 --> 11:41.617
{\an3}OH, YES.

11:41.700 --> 11:42.284
COULD YOU TEACH ME?

11:42.368 --> 11:44.453
IT WOULD BE MY PLEASURE.

11:44.537 --> 11:45.413
{\an1}HOP ON!

11:45.496 --> 11:47.289
(<i> Heff continues screaming</i> )

11:47.373 --> 11:50.376
THERE'S A NICE ROCK QUARRY
JUST A FEW BLOCKS FROM HERE

11:50.459 --> 11:52.336
WHERE THE CUTTERS
MAKE THEIR LIVING.

11:52.420 --> 11:53.421
BUT THEY'LL LET US
JUMP AROUND THERE.

11:53.504 --> 11:55.965
(<i> Heff catches breath</i> )

11:56.048 --> 11:58.092
(<i> resumes screaming</i> )

11:59.093 --> 11:59.343
[Captioning sponsored by THE
U.S. DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION]

12:12.773 --> 12:13.399
Oscar, Oscar, Oscar.

12:13.482 --> 12:16.277
{\an5}Get out of my life, Felix.

12:16.360 --> 12:17.820
HEY, MOM AND DAD.

12:17.903 --> 12:19.363
WOW, WHAT A WORKOUT.

12:19.447 --> 12:21.615
HEFFER, THERE'S SOMETHING

12:21.699 --> 12:23.492
{\an1}YOUR FATHER WANTS
TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT.

12:23.576 --> 12:26.745
YEAH, MOM,
AFTER DINNER.

12:26.829 --> 12:29.665
{\an1}DEAR, DON'T YOU THINK
YOU SHOULD SAY SOMETHING?

12:29.748 --> 12:31.667
I'LL TALK TO HIM LATER.

12:31.750 --> 12:34.086
♪ DUM, DUM, DUM ♪

12:34.170 --> 12:35.671
HEY!

12:35.754 --> 12:37.673
{\an1}HEY, BUB,
COMING THROUGH.

12:37.756 --> 12:39.008
HUH?

12:41.802 --> 12:43.721
OH, HONEY, IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

12:43.804 --> 12:45.764
WELL, SUGARPLUM, IT WILL BE

12:45.848 --> 12:48.517
{\an1}AFTER WE PUT
A LITTLE WORK INTO IT.

12:48.601 --> 12:49.894
RIGHT, KIDS?

12:49.977 --> 12:51.103
SURE THING, DADDY.

12:51.187 --> 12:53.272
{\an1}MOM, DAD!

12:53.355 --> 12:55.983
VERMIN!

12:56.066 --> 12:58.986
THERE'S VERMIN IN MY ROOM!

12:59.069 --> 13:01.697
YEAH, YEAH, THEY SIGNED A LEASE.

13:01.780 --> 13:03.699
SIGNED A LEASE?

13:03.782 --> 13:05.367
UNDERSTAND, SON...

13:05.451 --> 13:08.704
{\an1}ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY
LISTEN UP AND LISTEN GOOD.

13:08.787 --> 13:10.206
I HAVE BEEN LAID OFF.

13:10.289 --> 13:11.707
TIMES ARE TOUGH.

13:11.790 --> 13:14.919
THIS FAMILY WILL HAVE
TO MAKE SACRIFICES.

13:15.002 --> 13:17.379
{\an1}SON, YOU'RE JUST NOT PULLING
YOUR WEIGHT AROUND HERE

13:17.463 --> 13:20.883
SO WE RENTED YOUR ROOM.

13:20.966 --> 13:22.468
BUT, DAD...

13:22.551 --> 13:24.512
DON'T HAVE A COW.

13:24.595 --> 13:28.224
YOUR MOM FIXED UP THE TREE HOUSE
FOR YOU.

13:28.307 --> 13:29.308
PETER, GET ME ANOTHER SODA.

13:29.391 --> 13:31.310
GUESS THIS WILL BE OKAY.

13:31.393 --> 13:34.188
I HAD SOME GOOD TIMES

13:34.271 --> 13:36.398
{\an1}UP THERE
ALL BY MYSELF.

13:38.400 --> 13:39.401
SMALLER THAN I REMEMBER IT.

13:39.485 --> 13:42.363
♪ BE IT EVER SO... ♪

13:42.446 --> 13:43.781
(<i> wood cracking</i> )

13:43.864 --> 13:45.491
(<i> screaming</i> )

13:47.117 --> 13:49.078
OW.

13:49.161 --> 13:50.663
(<i> doorbell ringing</i> )

13:50.746 --> 13:52.081
Rocko:
OH, OW!

13:52.164 --> 13:53.749
SORRY, SPUNKY.

13:53.832 --> 13:55.876
ROCKO!

13:55.960 --> 13:58.462
{\an1}BLAZES, HEF, IT'S 2:00
IN THE MORNING.

13:58.546 --> 14:00.297
2:30, ACTUALLY.

14:00.381 --> 14:02.675
OOH, LEFTOVER PIZZA CRUST.

14:02.758 --> 14:05.678
HEF, WHAT'S GOING ON?

14:05.761 --> 14:08.597
WELL, MY PARENTS RENTED MY ROOM.

14:08.681 --> 14:10.015
THAT'S A TOUGH BREAK.

14:10.099 --> 14:11.100
I'M HITTING THE ROAD.

14:11.183 --> 14:15.854
{\an1}WOULD IT BE COOL IF I STAYED
HERE A COUPLE OF DAYS?

14:15.938 --> 14:17.314
MM...OKAY.

14:17.398 --> 14:18.399
YOU CAN SLEEP
ON THE COUCH.

14:18.482 --> 14:21.193
THANKS, ROCK.

14:21.277 --> 14:22.403
GOOD NIGHT, HEF.

14:22.486 --> 14:24.071
(<i> yawning</i> )

14:32.079 --> 14:33.872
NOW LISTEN HERE, TANKER TUSH.

14:33.956 --> 14:37.376
{\an1}YOU CAN PARK YOUR THUNDER CHEEKS
IN SOMEONE ELSE'S FACE

14:37.459 --> 14:38.419
'CAUSE I DESERVE
BETTER THAN THIS.

14:38.502 --> 14:42.381
<i>SAY-O-NA-RA,</i> BUTTERBALL.

14:48.387 --> 14:49.680
{\an1}ROCKO...

14:49.763 --> 14:51.849
ROCKO.

14:53.183 --> 14:55.644
WHAT IN THE..?

14:55.728 --> 14:57.646
HEF, WHAT NOW?

14:57.730 --> 14:58.480
YOUR COUCH RAN AWAY.

14:58.564 --> 15:01.025
CAN I SLEEP WITH YOU?

15:01.108 --> 15:04.111
OKAY, BUT JUST FOR TONIGHT.

15:04.194 --> 15:06.196
{\an1}YA-HOO!

15:06.280 --> 15:08.198
SLEEP OVERS!

15:28.927 --> 15:32.598
{\an1}OH, WELL, I GUESS
THIS WILL HAVE TO DO.

15:32.681 --> 15:34.933
(<i> snoring</i> )

15:35.768 --> 15:38.646
(<i> snoring grows louder</i> )

15:41.565 --> 15:43.984
{\an1}Man:
MAN ALIVE, SOMEBODY'S DYING.

15:44.068 --> 15:46.528
WHAT'S THAT NOISE?

15:49.531 --> 15:52.368
(<i> snoring stops</i> )

15:54.620 --> 15:57.539
(<i> snoring resumes</i> )

16:00.751 --> 16:04.254
I KNEW THIS WOULD COME IN HANDY.

16:04.338 --> 16:05.339
(<i> electrical crackling</i> )

16:05.422 --> 16:07.716
BLAZES.

16:07.800 --> 16:09.009
MM.

16:09.093 --> 16:10.344
SHEILA?

16:17.726 --> 16:20.479
(<i> alarm ringing</i> )

16:20.562 --> 16:22.564
NOTHING LIKE
A GOOD NIGHT'S SLEEP.

16:22.648 --> 16:25.901
I HAD THIS WILD DREAM.

16:25.984 --> 16:28.195
ELECTRIC EELS WERE
BITING MY BUTT.

16:31.490 --> 16:33.367
TIME FOR MY BEAUTY BATH.

16:36.453 --> 16:37.871
(<i> water running</i> )

16:37.955 --> 16:40.624
(<i> Heffer singing off-key</i> )

16:47.756 --> 16:51.510
{\an1}AH, NOTHING LIKE
A HOT SHOWER TO START THE DAY.

16:51.593 --> 16:52.970
BATHROOM'S ALL YOURS.

16:53.053 --> 16:54.138
(<i> coughing</i> )

17:04.272 --> 17:06.942
(<i> screaming</i> )

17:11.488 --> 17:13.574
T-T-T-TOWEL.

17:14.657 --> 17:16.492
{\an3}UGH!

17:16.577 --> 17:19.038
IT'S A NIGHT... NIGHTMARE.

17:22.624 --> 17:27.421
MUST GET D-D-D-DRY.

17:34.219 --> 17:35.888
(<i> screaming</i> )

17:43.020 --> 17:45.898
(<i> rock music blaring</i> )

17:53.697 --> 17:54.490
HEY, ROCKO.

17:54.573 --> 17:56.950
WHAT HAVE YOU DONE?

17:57.034 --> 17:57.910
PRETTY COOL, HUH?

17:57.993 --> 18:01.371
{\an1}GAVE ALL YOUR DULL OLD STUFF
TO CHARITY.

18:01.455 --> 18:02.831
YOU...

18:02.915 --> 18:03.499
THANK ME OVER DINNER.

18:03.582 --> 18:05.667
I MADE US

18:05.751 --> 18:07.669
MY SPECIALTY.

18:07.753 --> 18:09.171
THE HEFFER DELUXE.

18:12.591 --> 18:15.385
HEF, THIS IS BONZA.

18:15.469 --> 18:16.637
WHAT'S IN IT?

18:16.720 --> 18:19.515
WELL, LET'S SEE...

18:19.598 --> 18:21.767
{\an1}THERE'S PICKLED BANANA SHAVINGS,
GYM SOCKS

18:21.850 --> 18:23.769
CANNED HAGGIS,
BEETLE BLADDERS

18:23.852 --> 18:25.562
{\an1}REAL PROCESSED HEAD CHEESE,
SALTPETER

18:25.646 --> 18:26.688
RECONSTITUTED CORN SWEAT

18:26.772 --> 18:29.733
THE FINEST BARLEY
AND HOPS...

18:30.651 --> 18:32.277
NOW WHERE WAS I?

18:32.361 --> 18:34.238
POTASH, SULPHUR,
MONOSODIUM GLUTAMATE

18:34.321 --> 18:37.658
{\an1}AND VEGETABLE CARTILAGE
AS A BINDING AGENT.

18:37.741 --> 18:40.202
{\an1}EH, EH, NO DESSERT UNTIL
YOU FINISH YOUR MEAL.

18:45.999 --> 18:49.002
VOILA! NOW, TIME FOR DESSERT.

18:49.086 --> 18:50.879
HEY, THIS SMELLS DELICIOUS.

18:50.963 --> 18:52.881
WHAT IS IT?

18:52.965 --> 18:54.591
HEFFER SOUFFLE

18:54.675 --> 18:56.134
A LA FLAMBE.

18:56.218 --> 18:57.719
(<i> phone ringing</i> )

18:57.803 --> 18:59.555
DON'T GET UP.

18:59.638 --> 19:00.430
IT'S PROBABLY FOR ME.

19:00.514 --> 19:04.393
{\an1}HEY, I DID DINNER,
SO YOU DO THE DISHES.

19:04.476 --> 19:06.436
{\an1}MOM?

19:06.520 --> 19:07.938
YES, IT'S ME.

19:08.021 --> 19:09.565
YOU WANT ME HOME?

19:09.648 --> 19:11.233
EXTRA MEALS?

19:11.316 --> 19:12.317
{\an1}WOW!

19:12.401 --> 19:17.573
{\an1}THE FACT IS, MOM,
MY NEW HOME IS HERE WITH ROCKO.

19:17.656 --> 19:19.658
{\an1}I'M GOING
TO STAY FOREVER...

19:19.741 --> 19:21.869
<i>AND EVER AND EVER...</i>

19:24.663 --> 19:26.790
(<i> snoring</i> )

19:41.179 --> 19:41.513
HEF?

19:41.597 --> 19:44.433
HEF?

19:44.516 --> 19:46.059
THERE YOU ARE.

19:46.143 --> 19:47.603
HEY, ROCKO.

19:47.686 --> 19:49.438
BOY, HEF...

19:49.521 --> 19:52.107
YOU'RE, YOU'RE...

19:52.190 --> 19:54.401
NAKED.

19:54.484 --> 19:55.777
HEF, WAIT!

19:55.861 --> 19:58.113
WHERE DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE GOING, BUB?

19:58.196 --> 19:59.907
OUT INTO MY BACKYARD.

19:59.990 --> 20:01.992
NOT LIKE THAT,
YOU'RE NOT.

20:02.075 --> 20:03.243
OH, YEAH?

20:03.327 --> 20:04.578
OUT OF MY WAY.

20:06.038 --> 20:07.956
OH, COBBLERS!

20:08.040 --> 20:09.917
CRIKEY!

20:10.000 --> 20:11.335
WHAT'S GOING ON?

20:22.304 --> 20:24.556
NICE BUICK.

20:26.683 --> 20:28.143
{\an1}HEF...

20:28.226 --> 20:29.394
WHAT'S GOING ON?

20:29.478 --> 20:32.272
ROCKO, LIVING HERE
HAS ALLOWED ME

20:32.356 --> 20:35.108
{\an1}TO EXPLORE NEW FACETS
OF MY PERSONALITY.

20:35.192 --> 20:37.027
I AM A NUDIST.

20:37.110 --> 20:38.153
BEV, I CAN'T BELIEVE IT!

20:38.236 --> 20:42.991
DO YOU KNOW WHAT THAT WEIRDO
NEXT DOOR IS UP TO?

20:43.075 --> 20:45.953
OH, SHUT UP
AND MIND YOUR OWN BUSINESS, ED.

20:46.036 --> 20:48.413
BEV, THEY'RE, WELL...

20:48.497 --> 20:51.416
{\an3}NUDE!

20:52.542 --> 20:54.419
OH, ED, YOU'RE RIGHT.

20:54.503 --> 20:57.047
OH, YES! THIS IS DISGUSTING!

20:57.130 --> 21:00.884
{\an1}QUICK, ED, GET THE TELESCOPE
OUT OF THE HALL CLOSET.

21:00.968 --> 21:04.262
{\an1}I WANT ALL YOU NUDISTS
OUT OF HERE THIS INSTANT.

21:06.181 --> 21:07.933
AND STAY OUT.

21:08.016 --> 21:10.686
AT LEAST I HAVE MY DIGNITY.

21:10.769 --> 21:12.980
HEFFER, YOU LISTEN,
AND YOU LISTEN GOOD.

21:13.063 --> 21:14.439
THIS IS MY HOUSE

21:14.523 --> 21:16.900
{\an1}AND YOU'VE TAKEN ADVANTAGE
OF MY HOSPITALITY

21:16.984 --> 21:18.068
FOR THE LAST TIME...

21:18.151 --> 21:21.530
Heffer:
<i>OH, BOY, AM I HUNGRY.</i>

21:21.613 --> 21:23.532
<i>GEE, HE SOUNDS A LITTLE ANGRY.</i>

21:23.615 --> 21:25.534
<i>MAYBE I SHOULD TELL HIM NOW.</i>

21:25.617 --> 21:27.953
{\an1}HEF, ARE YOU
LISTENING TO ME?

21:28.036 --> 21:30.038
UH...NO.

21:30.122 --> 21:33.792
{\an1}SORRY, ROCK, BUT THERE'S
SOMETHING I NEED TO TELL YOU.

21:33.875 --> 21:37.879
NOW DON'T TAKE THIS PERSONALLY,
BUT I'VE COME TO THE CONCLUSION

21:37.963 --> 21:39.631
THAT YOU'RE JUST TOO DIFFICULT
TO LIVE WITH.

21:39.715 --> 21:40.716
WHAT?

21:40.799 --> 21:41.925
ROCKO, I HOPE

21:42.009 --> 21:44.219
YOU'RE NOT
DISAPPOINTED.

21:44.302 --> 21:44.803
WE'RE STILL FRIENDS,
AREN'T WE?

21:44.886 --> 21:48.098
WE'LL ALWAYS BE FRIENDS.

21:49.349 --> 21:50.392
A-HA!

21:50.475 --> 21:51.935
DAD?

21:52.019 --> 21:52.769
{\an1}I KNEW IT.

21:52.853 --> 21:54.062
THIS IS A PIGSTY.

21:54.146 --> 21:57.399
YOUR DEAR MOTHER
INSISTED I COME HERE

21:57.482 --> 21:59.943
{\an1}AND BRING YOUR BIG,
BEEFY, BOVINE BUNS BACK HOME.

22:00.027 --> 22:03.238
OKAY. BE RIGHT
WITH YOU, POP.

22:03.321 --> 22:06.324
{\an1}WELL, OLD PAL,
TILL OUR PATHS CROSS AGAIN.

22:08.243 --> 22:10.245
SEE YOU TOMORROW, ROCK.

22:10.328 --> 22:11.872
HEY, PUT SOME TROUSERS ON.

22:11.955 --> 22:16.043
YOU CRAZY KID, YOU.

22:16.126 --> 22:18.253
(<i> whimpering</i> )

22:19.171 --> 22:24.134
{\an1}AH, SPUNKY, I'M GLAD
THAT'S OVER.

22:24.217 --> 22:26.428
{\an1}NOW FOR A PEACEFUL
NIGHT'S SLEEP.

22:26.511 --> 22:32.267
{\an5}Bev:
<i>ALL RIGHT, TIME TO PARTY,</i>
<i>YOU ANIMALS.</i>

22:32.350 --> 22:35.270
SPUNKY, IT'S MRS. BIGHEAD

22:35.353 --> 22:37.647
AND... AND THE NUDISTS!

22:37.731 --> 22:40.776
{\an5}Ed:
<i>BEV, WHAT ARE ALL THESE FREAKS</i>
<i>DOING HERE?</i>

22:40.859 --> 22:42.652
Bev:
<i>OH, SHUT UP, ED</i>

22:42.736 --> 22:46.114
<i>AND GET YOUR TROUSERS OFF</i>
<i>AND JOIN THE PARTY</i>

22:46.198 --> 22:49.493
{\an1}<i>'CAUSE WE'RE GOING TO BOOGIE</i>
<i>TILL THE SUN COMES UP.</i>

22:52.621 --> 22:54.790
